            <!-- INTRODUCTION -->
            <div style="background: #e3f2fd; padding: 25px; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-left: 5px solid #2196f3;">
                <h3 style="color: #1976d2; margin-bottom: 15px;">üìå What is Negation?</h3>
                <p style="line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                    Negation is how we make sentences <strong>negative</strong> - saying what is NOT happening, what does NOT exist, 
                    or what someone does NOT do.
                </p>
                <div style="background: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 5px; margin-top: 15px;">
                    <p style="line-height: 1.8;">
                        <strong>Examples in English:</strong>
                    </p>
                    <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px; line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li>I <strong>do not</strong> go</li>
                        <li>He is <strong>not</strong> here</li>
                        <li>She <strong>doesn't</strong> eat</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- SECTION 1: VERB NEGATION - PRESENT TENSE -->
            <div class="negation-section">
                <div class="negation-title">1. Present Tense Negation</div>
                <div class="negation-subtitle">Using "na" and "ne"</div>

                <div class="explanation">
                    <p>
                        In the <strong>present tense</strong>, Kurdish uses different negative particles depending on the verb form:
                    </p>
                    <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px; line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li><strong>na-</strong> prefix for present continuous (di- verbs)</li>
                        <li><strong>ne-</strong> prefix for simple present and subjunctive</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <h4 style="color: #2e7d32; margin: 25px 0 15px 0;">Present Continuous (di- verbs) ‚Üí na-</h4>

                <table class="comparison-table">
                    <thead>
